2. DEFINITIONS
================================================================================

2.1 "Software" means the Nebular OS computer program and all associated
    materials distributed by Licensor under this Agreement, including without
    limitation source code, object code, binary executables, container images,
    documentation, configuration files, schemas, migration scripts, and any
    corrections, updates, upgrades, or new releases that Licensor designates as
    subject to this Agreement, unless expressly provided under separate terms.

2.2 "Derivative Work" means any work based upon or incorporating the Software
    or any portion thereof, including without limitation modifications,
    adaptations, translations, merged or combined works, or any work whose
    creation requires permission under applicable copyright law. For clarity,
    a software product that statically or dynamically links to, embeds, wraps,
    or calls into the Software (including as a Rust crate dependency) constitutes
    a Derivative Work for purposes of this Agreement to the extent it incorporates
    or depends upon the Software.

2.3 "Distribution" means to make available, publish, disclose, transmit,
    deliver, sublicense, sell, offer to sell, rent, lease, lend, upload,
    post, share, or otherwise provide access to the Software or any Derivative
    Work to any third party, whether for consideration or gratuitously, including
    without limitation: (a) publishing source code in a public or private
    repository accessible to anyone other than Permitted Private Recipients;
    (b) distributing binaries, packages, or container images; (c) including
    the Software in a product made available to third parties; (d) making the
    Software available through a network where persons other than Permitted
    Private Recipients may obtain or use it; or (e) any act that would constitute
    "making available to the public" or "Veröffentlichung" under applicable
    copyright law.

2.4 "Permitted Private Recipients" means: (a) when You are a Natural Person
    Qualifying User, only You and members of Your household; or (b) when You
    are a Qualifying Non-Profit Organization, only Your employees, volunteers,
    contractors, and agents who require access solely to perform work directly
    for Your internal, non-commercial operations and who are bound by written
    confidentiality obligations at least as protective as this Agreement.

2.5 "Natural Person Qualifying User" means a human individual using the
    Software in a personal, private, non-commercial capacity, not as an employee,
    contractor, agent, or representative acting within the scope of employment
    or engagement with a For-Profit Entity, and not primarily for monetary or
    commercial advantage.

2.6 "Qualifying Non-Profit Organization" means a legal entity that: (a) is
    formally recognized as a non-profit, charitable, educational, or similar
    not-for-profit organization under the laws of its jurisdiction of
    incorporation or registration (including, by way of example, an organization
    described in Section 501(c)(3) of the United States Internal Revenue Code,
    a German gemeinnützige Organisation within the meaning of the German Fiscal
    Code (Abgabenordnung), or an equivalent status elsewhere); (b) is not
    organized or operated for the profit or financial benefit of private
    shareholders, members, or partners; (c) is not controlled, directly or
    indirectly, by a For-Profit Entity; and (d) does not operate a paid
    proprietary product or service tier that incorporates or depends upon the
    Software as a material component.

2.7 "For-Profit Entity" means any corporation, company, partnership, limited
    liability company, trust, association, government commercial enterprise, or
    other legal entity organized or operated for profit or the economic benefit
    of owners, shareholders, members, or partners, and any entity controlled
    by such an entity, as well as any sole proprietorship or unincorporated
    business operated for commercial advantage.

2.8 "Private Use" means use of the Software solely for Licensee's own internal
    purposes where: (a) the Software and any Derivative Work are not Distributed;
    (b) the Software is not used to provide a Hosted Service to any person or
    entity other than Permitted Private Recipients; (c) the Software is not used
    to develop, test, or deliver a product or service that is Distributed or
    offered to third parties; and (d) access credentials, endpoints, and
    interfaces exposing the Software are not made available to the general public
    or to any For-Profit Entity except as expressly permitted under a Commercial
    License Agreement.

2.9 "Hosted Service" means operating the Software (or a Derivative Work) on
    one or more servers, containers, virtual machines, or cloud instances such
    that users, applications, tenants, customers, or other third parties store,
    retrieve, or manage data through the Software's object storage API or library
    interfaces, whether directly or indirectly.

2.10 "Commercial Use" means any use of the Software that is not Permitted Use
     (as defined in Section 3.2), including without limitation any use by or
     for the benefit of a For-Profit Entity; any use in connection with revenue
     generation, fee-for-service offerings, advertising-supported services,
     internal production infrastructure of a For-Profit Entity, consulting or
     managed services for third parties, evaluation for potential commercial
     deployment, benchmarking for competitive purposes, or any use intended to
