2.11 "Commercial License Agreement" means a separate written agreement executed
     by Licensor and Licensee (which may be confirmed by Licensor in writing in
     a Project Repository issue thread opened as a commercial license inquiry,
     or in a signed contract) that authorizes specified Commercial Use in exchange
     for fees and on terms set forth therein.

2.12 "Permitted Use" has the meaning set forth in Section 3.2.

2.13 "Licensor Reserved Rights" has the meaning set forth in Section 4.

2.14 "Security Vulnerability" means any flaw, weakness, misconfiguration, defect,
     or condition in the Software that could reasonably be exploited to compromise
