================================================================================

3.1 Conditional Grant. Subject to Your ongoing compliance with all terms of
    this Agreement, Licensor grants You a limited, non-exclusive,
    non-transferable, non-sublicensable, revocable, worldwide license to use
    the Software only as Permitted Use.

3.2 Permitted Use. "Permitted Use" means Private Use of the Software by exactly
    one of the following qualified Licensees, and only while all qualification
    criteria remain satisfied:

    (a) Natural Person Qualifying User — You are a natural person acting in
        a personal, private, non-commercial capacity; or

    (b) Qualifying Non-Profit Organization — You are a Qualifying Non-Profit
        Organization using the Software exclusively for Your internal
        operations that are not Commercial Use;

    AND in either case:

    (c) Private — the use satisfies the definition of Private Use in Section 2.8;

    (d) Non-Commercial — the use is not Commercial Use and is not primarily
        intended for or directed toward monetary or commercial advantage; and

    (e) No Distribution — You do not Distribute the Software or any Derivative
        Work except as expressly allowed in Section 3.3.

3.3 Limited Internal Sharing. A Qualifying Non-Profit Organization may permit
    Permitted Private Recipients to access internally deployed instances solely
    for the organization's internal Private Use, provided the organization
    ensures compliance with this Agreement and remains liable for any breach by
    such recipients.

3.4 Scope of Permitted Use. Permitted Use explicitly includes, when all
    qualifications in Section 3.2 are met:

    (a) installing and running the Software as a self-hosted object storage
        service on infrastructure controlled by the Licensee;

    (b) compiling the Software and linking to it as a library dependency (including
        as the `nebular_os` Rust crate) within a private application that is not
        Distributed and is not used for Commercial Use;

    (c) modifying the Software for private internal use, provided modifications
        are not Distributed except to Licensor as contributions subject to
        Section 10; and

    (d) making a reasonable number of backup copies solely for disaster recovery
        of Permitted Use deployments, provided such copies remain under Your
        control and are not Distributed.

3.5 No Implied Rights. Any use not expressly granted is reserved by Licensor.
    Without limiting the foregoing, Permitted Use does NOT include Distribution,
    Commercial Use, public open source release, inclusion in products offered
    to third parties, Hosted Service operation for third parties, or use by
    any For-Profit Entity (including internal use), even if such use is
    non-public.


