    (d) sublicense, rent, lease, lend, sell, or transfer the Software or any
        rights therein except as expressly permitted;

    (e) use the Software in violation of applicable law, including export control,
        sanctions, data protection, and anti-spam laws;

    (f) use the Software to store, transmit, or process unlawful content or to
        interfere with third-party systems;

    (g) use the Software for any illegal activity or in furtherance of any
        unlawful purpose;

    (h) use the Software if You are a Terrorist Organization or are owned,
        controlled by, acting for, or providing material support to a Terrorist
        Organization;

    (i) circumvent, disable, or interfere with technical or contractual measures
        used to enforce this Agreement;

    (j) misrepresent Your qualification for Permitted Use or Your authorization
        for Commercial Use.

6.2 Competitive Use. Except under a Commercial License Agreement explicitly
    permitting otherwise, You shall not use the Software to develop or offer a
    competing object storage product or service for third parties.

6.3 No OSS Conversion. You shall not relicense, release, or contribute the
    Software or any Derivative Work under an open source license, "copyleft"
    license, or any license that would grant third parties rights broader than
    Permitted Use, except with Licensor's prior written consent.

6.4 Bug and Security Reporting; Prohibition on Exploitation. If You discover or
    become aware of any bug, defect, error, or Security Vulnerability in the
    Software, You must promptly report it to Licensor through the Project Issue
    Tracker, providing sufficient detail for Licensor to understand and reproduce
    the issue where reasonably possible. You shall not:

    (a) exploit any bug, defect, error, or Security Vulnerability to gain
        unauthorized access, exfiltrate data, disrupt systems, or cause harm;

    (b) use knowledge of any such issue to use the Software for illegal activity
        or to assist any third party in doing so;

    (c) publicly disclose a Security Vulnerability in a manner that enables
        exploitation before giving Licensor a reasonable opportunity to investigate
        and address it, except where required by applicable law; or

    (d) delay reporting a Security Vulnerability so that it may be exploited,
        weaponized, sold, or used for any purpose other than good-faith testing
        within the scope of Your Permitted Use or authorized Commercial Use.

    Good-faith security research strictly limited to systems You own or are
    expressly authorized to test, and conducted without causing harm or accessing
    third-party data without authorization, does not violate this Section 6.4
    provided all discovered issues are reported promptly through the Project Issue
    Tracker and are not exploited for unlawful purposes.

6.5 Terrorist and Sanctioned Use Prohibition. You shall not use, deploy, modify,
    distribute, or provide access to the Software, directly or indirectly, for the
    benefit of any Terrorist Organization or for any activity related to terrorism,
    violent extremism, or material support thereof. You shall not use the Software
    in violation of applicable sanctions, export control, or anti-terrorism laws.
    Any such use is void, constitutes immediate termination under Section 11, and
    may be reported to competent authorities.


